<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I use Emacs (evil-mode) for extensive note-taking but don&#39;t have much programming experience. Can someone help me with a function to copy visually selected text in org-mode to clipboard and exclude the org emphasis markers, e.g. selecting raw text <code>+string+</code> copies to clipboard just <code>string</code>? <code>org-copy-visible</code> by itself doesn&#39;t copy to system clipboard. Also, I don&#39;t want to think about whether to use <code>org-copy-visible</code> or <code>evil-yank</code>--99% of the time I just want to <code>evil-yank</code> and also don&#39;t want the emphasis markers copied to clipboard (e.g. copy paste to document or terminal).</p> <p>Basically:</p> <ul> <li><p>Should rely on <code>org-copy-visible</code> which probably does a better job than trying to parse selected text using regex</p></li> <li><p>Custom function or overloading <code>evil-yank</code> only for org-mode where <code>org-copy-visible</code> is relevant. I prefer to just use plain <code>evil-yank</code> in non-org-mode buffers instead of e.g. <code>my\evil-yank</code> that falls back to <code>evil-yank</code> since this is less efficient in scenarios where I&#39;m working with non-org-mode buffers.</p></li> </ul> <p>Much appreciated.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/gregorie12"> /u/gregorie12 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/138t8ik/noob_evilyank_and_orgcopyvisible_function/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/138t8ik/noob_evilyank_and_orgcopyvisible_function/">[comments]</a></span>